# Core has no production for `{ }` at all (they are Data-profile dict-literal delimiters), so a
# standalone brace pair with no dict grammar around it raises ol-unmatched-brace TWICE — once for
# the opening `{` and once for the closing `}` — since neither delimiter is ever paired by any
# Core production (spec/error-model.md ol-unmatched-brace; spec/data-structures.md dict literals).
{ }
